com.navis.framework.portal.cache

Interface IEntityCacheConfiguration

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    ILivePositionableCacheConfiguration, IScopedEntityCacheConfiguration, IYardCacheConfiguration
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractEntityCacheConfiguration, AbstractScopedEntityCacheConfiguration, ArgoAbstractEntityCacheConfiguration, BaseLivePositionableCacheConfiguration, DefaultLivePositionableCacheConfiguration, DefaultYardCacheConfiguration, DefaultYardCustomCacheConfiguration

    public interface IEntityCacheConfiguration
    This interface should be implemented by all the cache metafield providers. An entity cache metafield provider provides: 1. A list of entity metafields which need to be cached. 2. A list of related entities as well as their metafields which need to be added to cache. They can be direct relations (foreign keys in entity to be cached) or any related entity which is navigable from the current entity. 3. For fields from other entities it provides the fully qualified fields. 4. Common methods to create domain queries and fetch values of entities which is used during initial building of cache as well as during insert processing of cached entities
    Author:
    Arvinder Brar, 2016-01-29

      • getRelatedEntityNameKeyFieldMap

        java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.util.List<MetafieldId>> getRelatedEntityNameKeyFieldMap(java.lang.String inEntityName)
        For all foreign key fields for the given entity name in cache, returns map of foreign key entity and the metafieldId(s) in the current entity which holds that foreign key value. Usually there is only one but there can be multiple foreign keys for same entity like a WorkInstruction has multiple fields for Che entity (WI_ITV, WI_CHE, WI_NOMINATED_CHE and so on)
        Parameters:
        inEntityName - entity name
        Returns:
        map of foreign key entity as key and value as the list of metafieldIds in the current entity which holds that foreign key value

      • getQualifiedMetafieldIds

        @NotNull
java.util.List<MetafieldId> getQualifiedMetafieldIds(@NotNull
                                                               MetafieldId inMetafieldId,
                                                               @NotNull
                                                               java.lang.String inBaseEntity,
                                                               @NotNull
                                                               java.lang.String inEntityOfField)
        Returns a qualified metafield id with navigation path from cached entity name to the updated entity name
        Parameters:
        inMetafieldId - metafield id
        inBaseEntity - cached entity name
        inEntityOfField - entity to which the field belongs
        Returns:
        list of qualified metafield id with navigation path from cached entity name to the updated entity name. In most cases a single metafield will be returned. A list is only returned if one entity has multiple foreign key fields pointing to same entity, for example, WorkInstruction entity has multiple fields which hold reference to Che entity (WI_ITV, WI_CHE and so on) A field will only be added to the returned list if it is one of the desired fields.

      • getComponentFieldsWhichShouldTriggerRefresh

        @NotNull
java.util.List<MetafieldId> getComponentFieldsWhichShouldTriggerRefresh(@NotNull
                                                                                  java.lang.String inBaseEntity)
        Returns a list of component fields which always need to be refreshed. These are fields which contain hibernating entities as their constituent fields. For example, unitRouting is a component field (hibernate component Routing) of Unit entity which contains other entities like Routing points and Carrier Service. In such case if a field of the constituent entity is included as a cached field, say unitRouting.rtgPOD1.pointId, it does not come as part of update. the update contains a 'detached' Routing entity which only contains the gkeys of constituent entity fields. In such case it is better to re-fetch the cached object.
        Parameters:
        inBaseEntity - cached entity name
        Returns:
        list of component fields which should trigger refresh of cached object

      • shouldUpdateCauseAdditionOfCacheEntries

        @Nullable
Tuple<? extends java.io.Serializable,MetafieldId> shouldUpdateCauseAdditionOfCacheEntries(@NotNull
                                                                                                     java.lang.String inCachedEntityName,
                                                                                                     @NotNull
                                                                                                     java.lang.String inUpdatedEntityName,
                                                                                                     @NotNull
                                                                                                     ValueHolder inUpdatedValues)
        Checks if the the entity update would cause addition of new entry/entries to cache. If true, returns a Tuple of scope level and scope metsfield of the entity being updated else returns null. If a related entity is being updated and cached entity has multiple relations to same foreign key entity (for example WorkInstructions can have multiple relations to Che, intended Che, nominated Che and so on), then all the cached entities related to updated entity will be added irrespective of the relation CAUTION: Please note that there should be NO DB ACCESS or any other time consuming processing in this method as it is called for every update
        Parameters:
        inCachedEntityName - cached entity name
        inUpdatedEntityName - updated entity name
        inUpdatedValues - updated values
        Returns:
        a Tuple of scope level and metafield id of updated entity which has the scope information if

                                               java.lang.String inCachedEntityName,

                                               java.lang.String inUpdatedEntityName,

        Checks if the the entity update would cause removal of entry/entries from cache. If a related entity is being updated and cached entity has multiple relations to same foreign key entity (for example WorkInstructions can have multiple relations to Che, intended Che, nominated Che and so on), then all the cached entities related to updated entity will be removed irrespective of the relation CAUTION: Please note that there should be NO DB ACCESS or any other time consuming processing in this method as it is called for every update
        Parameters:
        inCachedEntityName - cached entity name
        inUpdatedEntityName - updated entity name
        inUpdatedValues - updated values
        Returns:
        true if the the entity update would cause removal of entry/entries from cache, false otherwise
